<h1>What’s happening with NovaMind?</h1>
<h2>The Company</h2>
<p>The company that has been developing NovaMind is being shut down and the NovaMind products and intellectual property are being transferred to a company managed by a former employee of NovaMind, who plans in due course to take the software forward in new directions, building on the legacy of the desktop versions of NovaMind.</p>
<p>There will be a <strong style="font-family:helveticaneueltstd-bd">transition period</strong> from the old company to the new one, ending on the <strong style="font-family:helveticaneueltstd-bd">26th of October 2016</strong>. </p>
<p>Not all products and development will be carried forward by the new company, so refunds are being offered to compensate for this. See below for details.</p>
<h2>Subscriptions</h2>
<p>The new company will offer subscriptions priced at $5 per month (if billed annually) that will allow the ongoing use of the desktop versions of NovaMind for Windows and Mac.</p>
<p>The following things will happen to the existing active subscriptions:</p>
<h3>Perpetual Subscription: </h3>
<ul style="font-size:1.3em">
<li>You will be emailed a NovaMind license key and a download link for a version of NovaMind you can continue using indefinitely. This will allow you to use the desktop versions of NovaMind (Windows and Mac). </li>
<li>These versions of NovaMind will include the features of the current versions of NovaMind for Windows and Mac at the time of the transition, but will not be updated beyond that point. </li>
<li>You can also request a full or partial refund of your subscription purchase. See below for details. </li>
</ul>
<h3>Annual Subscription: </h3>
<ul style="font-size:1.3em">
<li>As of the date of this announcement, no further renewals will be charged on your existing account, but the account will remain active until the end of the transition period. </li>
<li>If you choose to request a refund on the refund page, that will be processed at the end of the transition period. </li>
<li>If you do not request a refund and your subscription has already been paid up to beyond the end of the transition period (excluding any bonus time added to a subscription), we will give you a prorated refund for the portion of your subscription you have not used.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Monthly Subscription: </h3>
<ul style="font-size:1.3em">
<li>As of the date of this announcement, no further renewals will be charged on your existing account, but the account will remain active until the end of the transition period. </li>
<li>If you choose to request a refund on the refund page, that will be processed at the end of the transition period.</li>
</ul>
<p>To continue using NovaMind <strong style="font-family:helveticaneueltstd-bd">beyond the transition period</strong> and to receive updated versions as they are released, you will need a new subscription purchased through the new company. Sign up will be available in a couple of weeks or so.</p>
<h2>Subscription Products</h2>
<p>There are changes to the products that will be available during the transition period, and after the transition is complete.</p>
<ul style="font-size:1.3em">
<li>NovaMind for <strong style="font-family:helveticaneueltstd-bd">Windows Desktop</strong> and <strong style="font-family:helveticaneueltstd-bd">Mac OS X</strong> will continue to be live during the transition and will be included in the new subscriptions under the new company.</li>
<li>NovaMind <strong style="font-family:helveticaneueltstd-bd">Cloud/Android</strong> will be discontinued on the <strong style="font-family:helveticaneueltstd-bd">14th of September</strong>. If you have any documents stored online, we will email them to you.</li>
<li>NovaMind for <strong style="font-family:helveticaneueltstd-bd">Windows Modern</strong> (as available on the Windows Store) will be unpublished on the <strong style="font-family:helveticaneueltstd-bd">14th of September</strong> and will no longer be supported.</li>
<li>NovaMind for <strong style="font-family:helveticaneueltstd-bd">iPad</strong> development is officially cancelled, since the new company is refocusing on the core Desktop applications.</li>
</ul>
<p>Any other legacy versions of NovaMind will no longer be supported. Any products not included in the new subscription will no longer be supported </p>
<h2>Refunds</h2>
<p>If you have a current, active subscription to NovaMind, then you are eligible for a refund. We will be collecting the refund requests during the transition period, and processing them all at the end of the transition.</p>
<p>Please <a href="https://www.novamind.com/refund">click here</a> for further details and to apply for a refund.</p>
<p align="center"> <a href="https://www.novamind.com/refund"><img src="/static/NovaMind/apply-for-refund.png" width="300" height="55"></a></p>
<h2>A word from Gideon King, founder of NovaMind</h2>
<p>After 16 years of hard work on NovaMind and weathering many storms, it was clear that I needed to step away from the day to day stress of running the company and developing NovaMind, but I was determined to leave our customers in the best possible situation I could. </p>
<p>I am doing this by leaving the company in the capable hands of Patrick who worked on NovaMind for 5 years and fully understands my vision for NovaMind along with the inner workings of the products, and also by offering refunds out of my own pocket for those who believe they haven’t received full value from their NovaMind subscription.</p>
<p>The decision to move on from NovaMind was not made lightly, and there were many challenges to do so in the best possible way for our customers. There were many steps to the process and all sorts of issues that needed to be resolved before we could complete the transition, which meant that the process took a long time. Please <a href="https://www.novamind.com/founder-message">see here</a> for a full description of why and how we got to this point.</p>
<p align="center"> <a href="https://www.novamind.com/founder-message"><img src="/static/NovaMind/tellmemore.png" width="150" height="28"></a></p>
<h2>A word from the new owner</h2>
<p>Gideon has invited me to take over the NovaMind IP so that the product can continue to help people be more productive and more organized every day. As a previous employee of NovaMind (working on NovaMind 5 for Windows), and a daily NovaMind user, I have a deep understanding of the product but having stepped away from the company a while ago, I also have no illusions about the reality of the current situation.</p>
<p>The unfaltering vision to deliver the best mind mapping application anywhere has meant that a very small team spent an extraordinary amount of work trying to replicate a full blown mind mapping application on five different platforms. In hindsight this endeavor was simply not possible and resulted in promises which were never fulfilled.</p>
<p>Despite all of this, it’s telling that the desktop versions of NovaMind still compare confidently with other industry offerings and provide a real alternative for people who like to efficiently create beautiful mind maps with flexible layout options. At the minimum I intent to preserve this offering and in the longer term I hope that I can refocus any future development efforts on NovaMind’s strengths with a pragmatic approach.</p>
<p>I want to thank everyone who supported NovaMind in the past and I also want to thank Gideon personally. You have worked harder than anyone I know and it’s a testament to your character and integrity that instead of abandoning NovaMind customers you are offering refunds to all your supporters who were waiting for announced features while passing on the IP to give NovaMind a chance of a future.</p>
<p align="right">Patrick Klug</p>
<h2>Action Steps</h2>
<ul style="font-size:1.3em">
<li>If you use NovaMind Cloud / Android, we will email you a copy of your documents that you have stored online on the <strong style="font-family:helveticaneueltstd-bd">14th of September</strong> when those services are terminated.</li>
<li>If you have a current active NovaMind subscription and want to receive a partial or full refund, <a href="https://www.novamind.com/refund">click here</a></li>
<li>The subscription through the new company will be available in a couple of weeks or so. Please check back here to sign up. We will also send out an email to everyone on our mailing list.</li>
</ul>
<h2>If you need assistance</h2>
<p>If you have any queries about any of the above, please email support@novamind.com</p>
<p align="right">13 August 2016</p>
